    {
      "name": "WW2 Fighter (Axis)",
      "size": 6,
      "loco": "turboprop",
      "desc": "Single-seat, single-engine interceptor. Bf-109s, Fw-190s, and Macchis dominated early-war skies.",
      "notes": "Bf-109s from the Emil through the Gustav and Kurf\u00fcrst marks, Fw-190 W\u00fcrgers, Macchi C.202 Folgores, and Kawasaki Ki-61 Hiens. The Axis built fast, well-armed interceptors with excellent climb rates and devastating cannon armament. The Bf-109 alone fought from Spain in 1937 to Berlin in 1945 \u2014 more were built than any other fighter in history. She's the opposition your players face in every European and North African air combat scenario.",
      "toughLevel": 0,
      "armourLevel": -1,
      "speedLevel": -1,
      "handlingLevel": 1,
      "mods": {},
