    {
      "name": "Vietnam-Era Utility Helicopter",
      "size": 7,
      "loco": "vtol",
      "desc": "The sound of the rotors IS the war. Hueys, Pumas, and Mi-8s \u2014 the workhorse of every conflict since.",
      "notes": "UH-1 Hueys, UH-60 Black Hawks, SA 330 Pumas, Mi-8 Hips, and the utility helicopters that defined warfare from Vietnam to Afghanistan. The Huey's distinctive two-blade rotor beat is the soundtrack of an entire war. She carries troops, evacuates wounded, delivers supplies, provides door-gun fire support, and defines the helicopter warfare era. Every variant from medevac to gunship started with this airframe. Helicopter.",
      "toughLevel": 0,
      "armourLevel": -1,
      "speedLevel": 0,
      "handlingLevel": 2,
      "mods": {},
