    {
      "name": "Modern Multirole Fighter (Eastern)",
      "size": 9,
      "loco": "jet",
      "desc": "Long-range interceptor. Flankers, Fulcrums, and their export derivatives.",
      "notes": "Su-27 Flankers, Su-30s, Su-35s, MiG-29 Fulcrums, and their export derivatives. The Soviet and Russian answer to Western air superiority \u2014 arguably more manoeuvrable at close range, equipped with excellent missiles, and exported to dozens of air forces worldwide. The Flanker family keeps evolving and keeps being dangerous. She represents peer-level opposition for any modern air combat campaign. Night Vision.",
